Fix kart driving (Owner.Value race), VIP kart redesign, connected ground + roads

- KartController: driving silently failed because it checked the kart's Owner.Value
  the instant you sat, before the reference replicated (same race that hit the
  buildings). Now it detects the kart seat by attribute and WAITS for Owner.Value to
  resolve before starting the drive loop. KartService defers SetNetworkOwner until
  the unanchor commits, so ownership handoff is reliable.
- VIP kart: added a rear wing, neon underglow, sleek neon nose tip, and side skirts
  so the premium kart actually looks premium (not just a recolor).
- HubService: a big shared ground now links the plot row to the city (no more
  floating islands) with an east-west boulevard + a main street down to the centre,
  so you can drive from any plot to Brainrot City.

